Yes yes breaks heads, our 69th guest mix is live now featuring a young talent, Kid Breaks. He's a much acclaimed, 18 yrs old Breakbeat DJ / Producer from Peterborough, UK. His real name is Logan Wright-French and since getting his first controller at just 12 years old he has smashed his way into the global breakbeat scene and already played big festivals like Camp Bestival and Shambala alongside the likes of the Stanton Warriors and the Plump DJ's. 

After gaining two A levels in music tech at college the kid with the big sound and heart to match jumped into producing and his debut EP 'Timeless Transformations' released in 2023 to big complimentary reviews and his future is looking brighter than ever. So keep your eyes and ears on this one as he goes from strength to strength, with pure love in what he's doing shining from him as he delivers infectiously ear candy popping and inspiring live performances

From the opening acid stabs of Wicked Wes’ “DRUGS (Acid Mix),” this mix wastes no time setting the tone—raw, hypnotic, and dripping in underground energy. The bubbling 303s pave the way for The Darrow Chem Syndicate’s “Star Maidens” (Kid Panel Remix), which keeps the intensity high with its driving bass and celestial synths, making for an intergalactic rollercoaster of groove.

A highlight of the first half is Rabbit In The Moon’s “I Am The Future,” a legendary track that blends cyberpunk atmospheres with hypnotic spoken-word vocals, bringing a futuristic edge to the journey. This seamlessly blends into DJ Icey’s “Vibe Syren,” a track that feels like the mix’s heartbeat—classic Florida breakbeat vibes with a pulsing rhythm designed for movement.

As we push further, Ondamike’s “Damages (2021 Mix)” injects a tougher, club-ready edge, bridging into a moment of pure acid euphoria with The Autobots’ “Let Me Glue Your Acid Fantasy”—a hybrid banger that pulls from Bicep’s atmospheric sound while keeping breakbeat energy front and center.

The mix continues its evolution, flowing through high-energy selections like Huda Hudia & DJ30A’s “Grove The System” and The Bass Droppers’ “Shake For Me,” each one reinforcing the dynamic fusion of classic breakbeat and modern bass-driven production. Code Rising’s “Schizo Robo” is a late-set standout, injecting a darker, electro-tinged vibe before things heat up again with “Booty Bounce” by Rob-Myco813, delivering exactly what the title promises—a relentless, dancefloor-fueled workout.

As we approach the closing section, DJ Icey’s “Bass Valet” brings back the funkier side of breaks before Sharaz’s “Empire” and “Walls” by Just10 & Left/Right deliver a cinematic conclusion, blending deep, emotional melodies with hard-hitting percussion. And then, the mix signs off in style with Sharaz’s “Touch Me” (Nite Sky Remix), a nostalgic, vocal-driven track that perfectly ties together the journey—soulful yet electrifying.

Final Thoughts
This mix is a masterclass in breakbeat storytelling—melding acid, funk, and futuristic energy into a seamless ride. It’s a celebration of both classic Florida breakbeat and forward-thinking bass music, with a balance of nostalgia and innovation that keeps the energy fresh from start to finish. Whether you’re a seasoned breaks head or a newcomer to the genre, this mix delivers a high-octane journey through the underground sound.

🔥 Best For: Late-night dancefloors, deep headphone trips, or anyone who loves breakbeat with a side of acid.

track.description:
Space Cowboy resident Rumblemunk is up on this week's RIPEcast with his live set from Breakfast of Champions 2024! 

In his words "I’m not a turntable-ist or an OG breakbeat DJ/producer, but when your set is in between Cut Chemist and Elite Force, whaddya do?

This set starts with a supporting MC, blazes through a mash-up of Drummatic Twins re-releases (thanks Nick), followed by my BOC 2023 release Shake That Thing, stops in with some Nick Thayer, bounces through my Eminight’s Doom bootleg, then settles in for an Elite Force medley (thanks Simon) that ends with playing the CDJ like an instrument. Brass Monkey gets us back on track heading towards a half time grind and shake, then resetting with a classic breakbeat, ending with my latest release, a Tears For Fears bootleg.

Thank you for all the love and support at this year’s BOC. Hope you enjoy the set and the memories!" - Rumblemunk
